# wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Recommended_applications has some great recommendations

# command-line
Rules: must be small, fast, and scriptable

conky - pipe to dzen for text status bar
dot - graph drawing
dzen - status bar
epub.py - command-line epub reader - github.com/rupa/epub
evince - powerful document viewer
exa - a modern replacement for ls
Exiv2 - image metadata editor
Feh - image viewer
Gifify
GraphicsMagick - displaying, converting, and editing raster image and vector image files (script addons: http://www.fmwconcepts.com/imagemagick/index.php)
graphviz - draw graphs
htop - alternative to top, more powerful
imagemagick
irssi
lm_sensors - monitor hardware temperature
mc - midnight commander
moc/mocp - command-line music player, run `mocp` for the client
mpg123 - command-line mpeg-audio player
mpv - media player
mutt - email
ncdu - disk usage
newsboat - rss
ogg123 - command-line ogg player
pandoc - universal markdown converter
parcellite - X clipboard (works in I3, icon bottom-right)
pdfgrep - search multiple pdfs for text
powertop - find battery savings
rdictcc - dictionary (https://github.com/tsdh/rdictcc)
recordmydesktop - simple tool, records to .ogv. use --windowid
remind - calender (https://www.roaringpenguin.com/products/remind)
Scrot - screen capture tool
sox - command line audio
spacemacs - vim+emacs
svox pico2wave - great text-to-speech!
tikz - draw graphs
tmux
unison - file synchronisation (https://www.cis.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison/)
vlc - more powerful than cvlc, type help to see commands. instant support for internet radio (mp3, mp3a, ...)
xdotool - cmdline mouse automation
zathura - simple document viewer
zsh

# network tools
iptrafng
nmap
tcpdump
wireshark

# GUI
gimp
inkscape
ttrss
firefox:
- ublock origin with everything blocked as default
- keyboard shortcuts to reorder tabs
https://obsproject.com/

windowed environment
--------------------
use mouse keys (keypad controls mouse)
